From 53d6742ae27cbeae4c7b991556875ec4e6e2c207 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 09:49:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 073/309] platform_profile: Move core out of ACPI

The platform profile class is useful for firmware interfaces that are not
backed by ACPI.  Keeping the core under CONFIG_ACPI_PLATFORM_PROFILE
forces non-ACPI users to depend on ACPI and prevents the class device from
being built when ACPI is disabled.

Introduce a generic PLATFORM_PROFILE symbol, build the core from
drivers/platform/, and switch existing users to select it.  Keep the
legacy ACPI aggregate files optional inside the core so
/sys/class/platform-profile remains available with CONFIG_ACPI=n or when
ACPI is disabled at runtime.

Signed-off-by: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
---
 drivers/acpi/Kconfig                          |  3 --
 drivers/acpi/Makefile                         |  1 -
 drivers/platform/Kconfig                      |  4 ++
 drivers/platform/Makefile                     |  2 +
 drivers/{acpi => platform}/platform_profile.c | 51 ++++++++++++++++---
 drivers/platform/surface/Kconfig              |  2 +-
 drivers/platform/x86/Kconfig                  |  8 +--
 drivers/platform/x86/amd/pmf/Kconfig          |  2 +-
 drivers/platform/x86/dell/Kconfig             |  4 +-
 drivers/platform/x86/hp/Kconfig               |  2 +-
 drivers/platform/x86/lenovo/Kconfig           |  6 +--
 drivers/thermal/intel/int340x_thermal/Kconfig |  2 +-
 12 files changed, 62 insertions(+), 25 deletions(-)
 rename drivers/{acpi => platform}/platform_profile.c (96%)

